'''Arjun "6ix" Ivatury''' (born February 17, 1991) is an Indian-American<ref>{{cite news|last1=C.M.|first1=Emmanuel|title=Behind the Boards: 6ix, Logic’s Producer|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2016/01/behind-the-boards-6ix-logics-producer/|accessdate=14 March 2017|publisher=XXL|date=14 January 2017}}</ref> [[record producer]] mostly known for his work in [[Gaithersburg, Maryland]] with rapper [[Logic (musician)|Logic]] as his in-house producer.<ref>{{cite news|last1=C.M.|first1=Emmanuel|title=Behind the Boards: 6ix, Logic’s Producer|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2016/01/behind-the-boards-6ix-logics-producer/|accessdate=14 March 2017|publisher=XXL|date=14 January 2017}}</ref> Other artists he has worked with include [[Dizzy Wright]], Michael Christmas, QuESt, and Jessica Andrea. He is associated with the independent record label [[Visionary Music Group]].

== Work with Logic (late 2009 - Present) ==
6ix is best known for his work with [[Gaithersburg, Maryland]] rapper [[Logic (musician)|Logic]] (2010 – present) for whom he has produced over 43 songs, including eleven from [[Logic (musician)|Logic's]] latest mixtape [[YSIV]]. The first song [[Logic (musician)|Logic]] and 6ix produced together was Love Jones from Logic's first mixtape.

6ix is a native of [[Bowie, Maryland]].<ref>https://www.washingtonian.com/2015/03/01/a-young-biracial-rapper-from-dc-is-the-next-big-thing/</ref> His father is a doctor; his mother is an engineer; his older brother is an aerospace engineer.<ref>http://www.mishthimusic.com/post/137250184937/6ix-otherwise-known-as-arjun-ivatury-is-a Origins of Logic and Producer 6s Working Relationship</ref><ref>http://theunn.com/2017/12/arjun-ivatury-wins-grammy-nomination/</ref> Before he became a full-time producer, 6ix attended the [[University of Maryland, College Park]], where he majored in neurology and physiology. In his senior year he dropped out of college in 2013 to move to Los Angeles with Logic to pursue a career in music production; he was 30 credits shy of his degree.<ref>{{cite news|last1=C.M.|first1=Emmanuel|title=Behind the Boards: 6ix, Logic’s Producer|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/news/2016/01/behind-the-boards-6ix-logics-producer/|accessdate=14 March 2017|publisher=XXL|date=14 January 2017}}</ref>He was nominated for Grammys for the first time for producing the song [[1-800-273-8255]] by Logic featuring [[Alessia Cara]] and [[Khalid (singer)|Khalid]]. In an interview with SlimShady magazine, he reportedly said that Richik Dadhich is his greatest fan. 
===YSIV===
He is also the executive producer of Logic's latest album "YSIV" released on September 28, 2018 and is also collaborating with Logic for his upcoming project called "Ultra 85".

