{{Infobox football biography | name = A Mít | fullname = A Mít | image = | caption = | birth_date = 1997 (age 18) | birth_place = [[Kon Tum]], [[Vietnam]] | height = {{height|m=1.67}} | currentclub = [[SHB Đà Nẵng F.C.]] | clubnumber = 8 | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = 2009–2010 | youthclubs1 = [[Hoang Anh Gia Lai – Arsenal JMG Academy|HAGL – Arsenal JMG Academy]] | youthyears2 = 2013–2016 | youthclubs2 = [[SHB Đà Nẵng F.C.|SHB Đà Nẵng]] | years1 = 2016– | clubs1 = [[SHB Đà Nẵng F.C.|SHB Đà Nẵng]] | caps1 = 32 | goals1 = 1 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | pcupdate = 2 October 2018 | ntupdate = }}
'''A Mít''' (born 1997) is a [[Vietnam]]ese [[association football|footballer]] of ethnic [[Degar]] descent who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[V-League (Vietnam)]] club [[SHB Đà Nẵng F.C.]].<ref>{{soccerway|mit-a/435760}}</ref>
==Early life== A Mít was born one of eight children to a poor [[Degar]] family of melon farmers in [[Kon Tum]]. At the age of just 12 A Mít traveled to [[Pleiku]] to join the [[Hoang Anh Gia Lai – Arsenal JMG Academy|HAGL – Arsenal JMG Academy]]. However A Mít's small size and frequent injuries and sicknesses caused him to quit and go back to his families farm. A couple years latter a scout from [[SHB Đà Nẵng F.C.|SHB Đà Nẵng]] took notice and invited A Mít to the club's academy. A Mít showed impressive improvement and in 2016 made his league debut.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tiền vệ A Mít (SHB Đà Nẵng): Người con núi rừng làm dậy sóng sông Hàn|url=http://bongdaplus.vn/tin-tuc/viet-nam/v-league/tien-ve-a-mit-shb-da-nang-nguoi-con-nui-rung-lam-day-song-song-han-1511161604.html|author=Ngọc Anh|website=Bong Da Plus|date=20 April 2016|accessdate=12 May 2016|language=Vietnamese}}</ref>
