{{Orphan|date=February 2013}} {{Taxobox | domain = [[Eukaryota]] | genus = '''''Kakabekia''''' | genus_authority = E.S. Barghoorn & S.A. Tyler, 1965 | type_species = '''''Kakabekia umbellata''''' | type_species_authority = Barghoorn & Tyler, 1965 | subdivision_ranks = [[Species]] | subdivision = *''K. barghoorniana'' <small>S.M.Siegel, 1968</small> *''K. edouardii'' <small>Locq. 1979</small> *''K. eduardi'' <small>Locq et al.</small> *†''K. flabelliformis'' <small>P.K. Maithy et al.</small> *†''K. rarea'' <small>P.K. Maithy et al.</small> *†''K. umbellata'' <small>Barghoorn & Tyler, 1965</small> }}
'''''Kakabekia''''' is an about two billion-year-old fossil genus of [[microorganism]] from the [[Gunflint Chert]]. ''[[Kakabekia barghoorniana]]'' is a living fossil of this genus.<ref name=Siegel>{{cite journal|first1=B.Z.|last1=Siegel|first2=S.M.|last2=Siegel|title=Biology of the Precambrian Genus Kakabekia: New Observations on Living ''Kakabekia barghoorniana''|journal=[[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America]]|date=October 1970|volume=67|issue=2|pages=1005–1010|jstor=60032|pmc=283305|pmid=16591868}}</ref>
