{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox adult biography | name = Timo Aaltonen | birth_name = Timo Antero Aaltonen | birth_date = 11 April 1969 | birth_place = [[Vehmaa]], [[Finland]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Finnish | spouse = | height = 189-cm | weight = 130 kg | ethnicity = | alias = | website = }} '''Timo Antero Aaltonen''' (born 11 April 1969 in [[Vehmaa]], [[Southwest Finland]]) is a 189-cm tall [[Finland|Finnish]] [[shot putter]] who weighs 130&nbsp;kg and competes for [[Turun Urheiluliitto]], which is the same club that [[Paavo Nurmi]] ran for. He competed and won a [[gold medal]] at the [[2000 European Indoor Athletics Championships]] with a qualifying put of 20.57&nbsp;m and a final put of 20.62&nbsp;m.
Aaltonen was the 13th member to be inducted into the [[20 meter club]] after he putted the shot 20.12&nbsp;m in a competition on 20 June 1998 in [[Kuortane]], [[Finland]].
